Q.  The quality of your shots seemed to improve in the second set.
 
ALBERT COSTA:  Yeah, at the beginning, he was playing a little harder, and I was like a little scared and playing with no confidence.  But then I start to realize that if I am not aggressive, I'm gonna lose, so I start to change some things and I start to hit faster.  So if I miss, I miss, but I cannot stand in the baseline, like playing with no power, so... 
 

